        "episode_id": "ep-4a1a673a7005a6b5",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "Here's how I think about it. A good on-call rotation is designed so that waking up is rare, and when it happens the response is obvious. We've seen this play out at teams using Datadog. What used to feel like an exception is honestly the median case now.",
